description.narrative: The CO continued to recognize how “nurturing care” is critical for a child’s development, encompassing good health and nutrition, responsive caregiving and opportunities for early learning. In 2020, the main interventions focused on parents and caregivers who play a central role in providing children with a sound nurturing environment, especially during the period from pregnancy to the start of primary school (i.e. 6 years). Steps were taken to enhance parents’ knowledge on exclusive breastfeeding and care practices for prematurely born infants, while also increasing access to inclusive ECE services for children with disabilities and special education needs. | Status:Met | As-of Date:19/01/2021
